==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English [[hopen]], from Old English [[hopian]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/həʊp/}}
*{{AHD|/hōp}}

===Verb===
'''to hope'''

#To want some thing to happen.
#: ''I hope everyone likes this definition, but I don't expect it.''

====Translations====
*Czech: [[doufat]]
*Dutch: [[hopen]]
*[[Esperanto]]: [[esperi]]
*Estonian: [[lootus]]
*Finnish: [[toivoa]]
*French: [[espérer]]
*German: [[hoffen]]
*Italian: [[sperare]]
*Lithuanian: [[trokšti]], [[viltis]]
*Spanish: [[esperar]]

===Noun===
'''hope'''

# (''uncountable'') The belief that something hoped for can happen.
#: ''I still have some hope that I can get to work on time.''
# (''countable'') Something which may cause something hoped for to happen.
#: ''We still have one hope left: my roommate might see the note I left on the table.''

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[hoop]] (1,2)
*[[Esperanto]]: [[espero]]
*Estonian: [[lootma]]
